# Database Rules

References:

- docs/database-design.md
- docs/enums.md
- docs/tech-architecture.md

---

# Database Engine

Primary Database

- PostgreSQL

ORM

- Entity Framework Core

---

# Source Of Truth

Database schema must follow:

docs/database-design.md

Do not invent tables.

Do not invent columns.

Do not invent relationships.

If schema changes:

Update documentation first.

Then update code.

---

# Entity Rules

One entity = one table.

Examples:

User

AffiliateLink

Order

WithdrawRequest

CommissionTransaction

AuditLog

---

# Naming Conventions

Tables

snake_case

Examples:

```sql
users
orders
affiliate_links
withdraw_requests
```

---

Columns

snake_case

Examples:

```sql
created_at
updated_at
available_balance
```

---

Primary Keys

```sql
id
```

UUID preferred.

---

Foreign Keys

Pattern:

```sql
user_id
order_id
withdraw_request_id
```

---

# Audit Columns

Every table must contain:

```sql
created_at
updated_at
```

Optional:

```sql
created_by
updated_by
```

---

# Soft Delete Rules

Default:

No soft delete for MVP.

Use hard delete only if business allows.

Critical tables:

- users
- orders
- withdrawals

should generally remain historical.

---

# Migration Rules

All schema changes require migration.

Never modify existing migrations.

Always create new migration.

Good:

```bash
dotnet ef migrations add AddWithdrawalBankInfo
```

Bad:

Editing old migration files.

---

# Entity Configuration Rules

Use:

```csharp
IEntityTypeConfiguration<T>
```

One configuration file per entity.

Examples:

```text
UserConfiguration.cs
OrderConfiguration.cs
```

---

# Fluent API Rules

Use Fluent API.

Preferred:

```csharp
builder.Property(x => x.Email)
       .HasMaxLength(255)
       .IsRequired();
```

Avoid DataAnnotations.

---

# Relationship Rules

Explicitly define relationships.

Good:

```csharp
builder
 .HasOne(...)
 .WithMany(...)
```

Avoid relying on EF conventions alone.

---

# Index Rules

Create indexes for:

- user_id
- order_id
- status
- created_at

Examples:

```csharp
builder.HasIndex(x => x.UserId);
```

---

# Financial Data Rules

Never use:

```csharp
float
double
```

Use:

```csharp
decimal(18,2)
```

Examples:

- commission_amount
- cashback_amount
- available_balance

---

# Enum Rules

Database values must map to:

docs/enums.md

Never hardcode magic numbers.

Bad:

```csharp
status = 2;
```

Good:

```csharp
status = OrderStatus.Approved;
```

---

# Transaction Rules

Must use transactions when:

- Updating balances
- Approving withdrawals
- Processing commissions
- Processing webhook events

Example:

```csharp
BeginTransactionAsync()
CommitAsync()
RollbackAsync()
```

---

# Concurrency Rules

Financial operations require protection.

Consider:

- Row locking
- Concurrency tokens

Critical operations:

- Withdrawal approval
- Commission settlement

---

# Query Rules

Read-only queries:

```csharp
AsNoTracking()
```

Always paginate large result sets.

Never load entire tables.

---

# Pagination Rules

Default page size:

```text
20
```

Maximum page size:

```text
100
```

---

# Seed Data Rules

Allowed:

- Admin User
- Enum Reference Data

Do not seed fake business transactions.

---

# Backup Rules

Production database:

- Daily backups
- 30-day retention

Never run destructive scripts without backup.

---

# Performance Rules

Avoid:

```csharp
.ToList()
```

before filtering.

Prefer:

```csharp
.Where(...)
.Select(...)
```

before execution.

---

# Security Rules

Never store:

- Plain text passwords
- API secrets
- OAuth secrets

Passwords (if used) must be hashed.

Sensitive data should be encrypted when necessary.

